pageTitle: ThinkPad 11b/g/n Wireless LAN Mini-PCI Express Adapter II for Windows Vista (32-bit, 64-bit) - ThinkPad - Lenovo Support (FI)
textBeforeTable: The following versions have been released to date. Access Connections for each of those versions are also available. Check the product version in the Details Pane. Select ThinkPad Wireless LAN Adapter Software. Select Organize, select Layout, then select Details Pane. The Details Pane will be shown at the bottom of screen. Make sure "View by Category" is selected, and click Uninstall a program. Click Start, then click Control Panel. To check the version of software, please perform the following steps: Determining which version is installed   Follow the instructions on the screen to complete uninstallation and restart the computer. Select ThinkPad Wireless LAN Adapter Software, and click Uninstall/Change. Make sure "View by Category" is selected, and click Uninstall a program. Click Start, click Control Panel. Start Windows and logon with administrative privileges. Uninstallation Instructions   At the command line, execute setup.exe with the -S option. Example: [Path where the files were extracted]\setup -S In step 11 of the "Installing files" section, uncheck the checkbox next to "Install .... now", and then click Finish to cancel installation. Refer to the "Manual Install" section, and download and extract the files. Note: This procedure is intended for system administrators only.. Silent Installation
textAfterTable: Limitations You may see two "ThinkPad Wireless LAN Software" names in "Programs and Features" when you update install this package over the existing driver on your system. This will not affect Wireless LAN functionality.
